# Investigation Report: Duplicate Response Headers in Envoy Filter Pipeline

## Summary

Response headers configured via `response_headers_to_add` in route configuration are duplicated in local replies generated by the router filter. This occurs because `finalizeResponseHeaders()` is called twice in the local reply code path—once explicitly in the filter manager and again implicitly when the `modify_headers_` callback (which itself contains a `finalizeResponseHeaders()` call) is invoked.

## Root Cause

The root cause is the **double invocation of `finalizeResponseHeaders()`** in the local reply handling path. This happens because:

1. **In router.cc (lines 444-461)**: The router filter creates a `modify_headers_` callback that includes an explicit call to `finalizeResponseHeaders()`:
   ```cpp
   modify_headers_ = [this](Http::ResponseHeaderMap& headers) {
     // ... other code ...
     route_entry_->finalizeResponseHeaders(headers, callbacks_->streamInfo());
   };
   ```

2. **In filter_manager.cc (lines 1123-1129, 1072-1078, 1156-1162)**: When constructing the local reply, the filter manager creates a lambda that calls `finalizeResponseHeaders()` directly AND then calls the `modify_headers_` callback:
   ```cpp
   [this, modify_headers](ResponseHeaderMap& headers) -> void {
     if (streamInfo().route() && streamInfo().route()->routeEntry()) {
       streamInfo().route()->routeEntry()->finalizeResponseHeaders(headers, streamInfo());  // FIRST
     }
     if (modify_headers) {
       modify_headers(headers);  // SECOND (contains finalizeResponseHeaders internally)
     }
   }
   ```

3. **In utility.cc (line 719)**: This lambda is invoked during the local reply preparation, causing both calls to `finalizeResponseHeaders()` to execute on the same response headers.

## Evidence

### Key Code References

**router.cc:442-461** - Router filter's `modify_headers_` initialization:
```cpp
// Initialize the `modify_headers_` function that will be used to modify the response headers for
// all upstream responses or local responses.
modify_headers_ = [this](Http::ResponseHeaderMap& headers) {
  if (route_entry_ == nullptr) {
    return;
  }
  if (modify_headers_from_upstream_lb_) {
    modify_headers_from_upstream_lb_(headers);
  }
  route_entry_->finalizeResponseHeaders(headers, callbacks_->streamInfo());  // LINE 453
  // ... rest of code ...
};
```

**filter_manager.cc:1123-1129** - sendLocalReplyViaFilterChain's header modification lambda:
```cpp
Utility::sendLocalReply(
    state_.destroyed_,
    Utility::EncodeFunctions{
        [this, modify_headers](ResponseHeaderMap& headers) -> void {
          if (streamInfo().route() && streamInfo().route()->routeEntry()) {
            streamInfo().route()->routeEntry()->finalizeResponseHeaders(headers, streamInfo());  // CALL 1
          }
          if (modify_headers) {
            modify_headers(headers);  // CALL 2 - contains another finalizeResponseHeaders()
          }
        },
```

**filter_manager.cc:1072-1078** - prepareLocalReplyViaFilterChain (identical pattern):
```cpp
prepared_local_reply_ = Utility::prepareLocalReply(
    Utility::EncodeFunctions{
        [this, modify_headers](ResponseHeaderMap& headers) -> void {
          if (streamInfo().route() && streamInfo().route()->routeEntry()) {
            streamInfo().route()->routeEntry()->finalizeResponseHeaders(headers, streamInfo());  // CALL 1
          }
          if (modify_headers) {
            modify_headers(headers);  // CALL 2 - contains another finalizeResponseHeaders()
          }
        },
```

**filter_manager.cc:1156-1162** - sendDirectLocalReply (identical pattern):
```cpp
Http::Utility::sendLocalReply(
    state_.destroyed_,
    Utility::EncodeFunctions{
        [this, modify_headers](ResponseHeaderMap& headers) -> void {
          if (streamInfo().route() && streamInfo().route()->routeEntry()) {
            streamInfo().route()->routeEntry()->finalizeResponseHeaders(headers, streamInfo());  // CALL 1
          }
          if (modify_headers) {
            modify_headers(headers);  // CALL 2 - contains another finalizeResponseHeaders()
          }
        },
```

**utility.cc:709-720** - prepareLocalReply invokes the modify_headers lambda:
```cpp
ResponseHeaderMapPtr response_headers{createHeaderMap<ResponseHeaderMapImpl>(
    {{Headers::get().Status, std::to_string(enumToInt(response_code))}})};

if (encode_functions.modify_headers_) {
  encode_functions.modify_headers_(*response_headers);  // LINE 719 - INVOKES THE PROBLEMATIC LAMBDA
}
```

**config_impl.cc:942-950** - RouteEntryImplBase::finalizeResponseHeaders implementation:
```cpp
void RouteEntryImplBase::finalizeResponseHeaders(Http::ResponseHeaderMap& headers,
                                                 const StreamInfo::StreamInfo& stream_info) const {
  for (const HeaderParser* header_parser : getResponseHeaderParsers(
           /*specificity_ascend=*/vhost_->globalRouteConfig().mostSpecificHeaderMutationsWins())) {
    // Later evaluated header parser wins.
    header_parser->evaluateHeaders(headers, {stream_info.getRequestHeaders(), &headers},
                                   stream_info);
  }
}
```

### Header Parser Behavior

**header_parser.cc:182-200** - Shows how headers are added based on `append_action`:
```cpp
switch (entry->append_action_) {
  PANIC_ON_PROTO_ENUM_SENTINEL_VALUES;
case HeaderValueOption::APPEND_IF_EXISTS_OR_ADD:
  headers_to_add.emplace_back(key, value);
  break;
case HeaderValueOption::ADD_IF_ABSENT:
  if (auto header_entry = headers.get(key); header_entry.empty()) {
    headers_to_add.emplace_back(key, value);
  }
  break;
case HeaderValueOption::OVERWRITE_IF_EXISTS:
  if (headers.get(key).empty()) {
    break;
  }
  FALLTHRU;
case HeaderValueOption::OVERWRITE_IF_EXISTS_OR_ADD:
  headers_to_overwrite.emplace_back(key, value);
  break;
}
```

When `finalizeResponseHeaders()` is called twice with `APPEND_IF_EXISTS_OR_ADD`:
- First call: Header is added
- Second call: Header is appended again (since it now exists), creating a duplicate

With `OVERWRITE_IF_EXISTS_OR_ADD`, the header is overwritten in both calls, but this still represents inefficient double-processing.

### Proto Definition Reference

**api/envoy/config/core/v3/base.proto:429-476** defines `HeaderValueOption`:
```protobuf
message HeaderValueOption {
  enum HeaderAppendAction {
    APPEND_IF_EXISTS_OR_ADD = 0;  // If header exists, append (default)
    ADD_IF_ABSENT = 1;
    OVERWRITE_IF_EXISTS_OR_ADD = 2;  // Overwrite if exists, add if absent
    OVERWRITE_IF_EXISTS = 3;
  }

  HeaderValue header = 1;
  google.protobuf.BoolValue append = 2 [deprecated = true];
  HeaderAppendAction append_action = 3;  // Defaults to APPEND_IF_EXISTS_OR_ADD
  bool keep_empty_value = 4;
}
```

The proto comment explicitly states:
